data.content:
Your code **does not use `Thread.Abort`**, so there's no `PlatformNotSupportedException` risk here. It will compile and run on .NET 8 as-is.

That said, the manual `Thread` management pattern should be modernized. Here's the recommended .NET 8 approach using `Parallel.ForEach`:

```csharp
public class SimpleWorker
{
    public void RunBatch(List<WorkItem> items)
    {
        Parallel.ForEach(items, item => Process(item));
    }

    private void Process(WorkItem item)
    {
        Thread.Sleep(100);
        item.Result = ComputeResult(item.Input);
    }
}
```

**Quick `Thread.Abort` migration reference** (for when you do encounter it elsewhere):

| .NET Framework pattern | .NET 8 replacement |
|---|---|
| `thread.Abort()` | `CancellationToken` + cooperative cancellation |
| `Thread` + `Abort` for timeout | `Task.Run` + `CancellationTokenSource.CancelAfter` |
| `catch (ThreadAbortException)` | `catch (OperationCanceledException)` |

`Thread.Abort` throws `PlatformNotSupportedException` in .NET 8 — all cancellation must be **cooperative** via `CancellationToken`.
